  "contract_summary": "This function initializes the AppArmor security labels on both sockets of a newly created socket pair. It acquires a reference to the current task's label via begin_current_label_crit_section, then for each socket, if its existing label differs from the current label, it releases the old label and assigns a new reference via aa_get_label. For AF_UNIX sockets, it additionally calls unix_connect_peers to set up the peer cross-reference (which itself manages refcounts on the peer labels). The function ends by releasing the temporary reference via end_current_label_crit_section. After this function, the socket contexts hold their own references to the labels; the sockets' ownership is implicitly tied to the sockets' lifetimes, and the labels are released when the sockets are freed.",
